MCP + CLI + Feishu Skill Demo

This demo shows how to:
1. Build a local MCP server that provides a skill scaffold tool.
2. Build a CLI client with multi-command workflow.
3. Generate both skill definition and Python executor.
4. Execute skill logic through Python and optionally push result to Feishu.

Project structure:

.
|- package.json
|- src/
|  |- mcp-server.js
|  `- cli.js
`- skills/
	`- <skill-name>/
		|- SKILL.md
		`- main.py

Quick start:

1) Install dependencies

npm install

2) Optional: create local env file from template

copy .env.example .env

3) Create a skill locally (MCP + CLI)

npm run skill:create -- --name zhihu-digest --description "Summarize top Zhihu answers and push daily"

This will generate:
- skills/zhihu-digest/SKILL.md
- skills/zhihu-digest/main.py

4) Push generated skill to Feishu

npm run skill:push -- --name zhihu-digest

5) Or create and push in one command

npm run skill:demo -- --name zhihu-digest --description "Summarize top Zhihu answers and push daily"

6) List all local skills

npm run skill:list

7) Execute Python logic of a skill

npm run skill:exec -- --name zhihu-digest --query "知乎今天热门 AI 回答"

8) Execute and push result to Feishu

npm run skill:exec -- --name zhihu-digest --query "知乎今天热门 AI 回答" --push

9) Daily digest (Zhihu only) one-shot test

npm run skill:daily:once

Zhihu source priority:
1. Public hot-list mirror (60s.viki.moe), no cookie/login required
2. Zhihu official hot-list API (cookie improves success)
3. Zhihu website hot pages (zhihu.com)
4. Optional custom JSON source

10) Daily digest schedule at 01:00 local time

npm run skill:daily -- --time 01:00

11) Start scheduler and also run immediately once

npm run skill:daily -- --time 01:00 --run-now

Optional parameters:

--webhook <url>     Override FEISHU_WEBHOOK_URL
--name <skill-name> Skill folder name
--description <text> Skill description
--push              Push to Feishu when using create command
--query <text>      Input query for exec command
--context <text>    Optional context for exec command
--python <path>     Python executable path for exec command
--time <HH:MM>      Daily push time for daily command, default 01:00
--once              Run daily digest once and exit
--run-now           Run once immediately, then keep scheduler running
--zhihu-hot-urls <urls> Comma-separated Zhihu hot page URLs (zhihu.com)
--zhihu-cookie <cookie> Optional cookie for Zhihu anti-bot/login pages
--zhihu-cookie-expires-at <iso> Optional expiry timestamp for reminder
--zhihu-json-url <url> Optional JSON source for Zhihu fallback
--zhihu-limit <n>   Max number of Zhihu items, default 10

Environment variable (optional):

FEISHU_WEBHOOK_URL=https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/bot/v2/hook/138fd2f9-73e9-4e0b-9abb-34a749ac3950

Environment loading:

- CLI automatically loads project-root .env before reading command flags.
- Command-line args still have highest priority.
- Recommended: keep ZHIHU_COOKIE and ZHIHU_COOKIE_EXPIRES_AT in .env.

Expected output:

- A new file: skills/<name>/SKILL.md
- A Feishu text message indicating generation success and preview content

Commands:

- npm run skill:create -- --name demo --description "..."
	- generate and save only
- npm run skill:create -- --name demo --description "..." --push
	- generate, save, and push
- npm run skill:push -- --name demo
	- push existing skills/demo/SKILL.md
- npm run skill:list
	- list all local skills
- npm run skill:exec -- --name demo --query "..."
	- run skills/demo/main.py and print JSON output
- npm run skill:exec -- --name demo --query "..." --push
	- run executor and push output to Feishu
- npm run skill:daily:once
	- pull Zhihu high-signal answers once and push to Feishu
- npm run skill:daily -- --time 01:00
	- run a local scheduler that pushes digest every day at 01:00

How MCP works in this demo:

1) CLI calls MCP tool skill_scaffold.
2) MCP server returns a structured SKILL.md template (capabilities, constraints, metadata).
3) CLI stores SKILL.md to skills/<name>/SKILL.md.
4) CLI also ensures skills/<name>/main.py exists as executable logic.
5) exec command runs main.py and gets runtime output.

In short:
- MCP defines and standardizes skill structure.
- Python file executes the real business logic.

Daily use-case notes (Zhihu):

- Public mirror: pulls the Zhihu hot list from 60s.viki.moe without any cookie/login.
- Zhihu API: official hot-list API is used as second source (cookie improves success).
- Zhihu website: tries zhihu.com hot pages and extracts question/answer links.
- Zhihu anti-bot: if blocked, pass --zhihu-cookie or ZHIHU_COOKIE.
- Fallback JSON: pass --zhihu-json-url (or env ZHIHU_JSON_URL).
- Scheduler: this is process-based scheduling, so keep the command running (or host with PM2 / task scheduler).
- Fault tolerance: if one source fails due to anti-bot limits, task still pushes digest with source error notes instead of crashing.
